############################################################################################

TO CONVERT THE CODE IN TO AN EXECUTABLE FILE(APPLICATION)...

1) CREATE A FOLDER ANYWHERE AND SAVE THE .py CODE INSIDE THE FOLDER.

2) OPEN THE FOLDER AND HOLD 'SHIFT' BUTTON AND THEN RIGHT CLICK ON THE EMPTY SPACE INSIDE THE FOLDER.

3) CLICK ON POWERSHELL/COMMAND PROMPT (THIS WILL ONLY APPEAR IF YOU HOLD 'SHIFT' AND 'RIGHT CLICK' ON THE SCREEN) 

4) MAKE SURE THAT YOU HAVE INSTALLED 'PYINSTALLER' OTHERWISE CLICK BELOW TO DOWNLOAD.
   LINK : https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/b4/83/9f6ff034650abe9778c9a4f86bcead63f89a62acf02b1b47fc2bfc6bf8dd/pyinstaller-4.2.tar.gz
   THEN TYPE 'pip install pyinstaller' (WITHOUT QUOTES).
   
5) TYPE 'pyinstaller' IN THE POWERSHELL/COMMAND PROMPT ( TO CHECK WHETHER PYINSTALLER IS SUCCESSIFULLY INSTALLED OR NOT)

6) TYPE 'pyinstaller --onefile "filename.py" '(WITHOUT QUOTES). {IF YOU HAVE ANY ICON TO ADD THEN SAVE THE IMACE IN THE .ico FORMAT IN THE SAME FOLDER
                                                                 THEN INCLUDE THIS AFTER --onefile -> ' -i "yourIconName.ico" ' 
                                                                 (with double quotes for yourIconName.ico) }

7) WAIT UNTIL IT IS PROCESSED, AFTER THAT YOUR APPLICATION WILL BE STORED IN THE 'DIST' FOLDER.

8) THIS APPLICATION CAN THEN BE SHARED TO OTHERS.
